{"article_id":"I9fYQRESIQYkGvKm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Back in 2009 , the US signed the Copenhagen Accord","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"and pledged","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that they would cut their emissions in 2025 by 30 %","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"compared to 2005 levels .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The world hissed","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"and booed ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and called it a failure .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Today , in an `` historic '' agreement","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"announced with China ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"the US are committing to cutting their emissions by less than that ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"( 26-28 % by the same date )","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"and the world is cheering .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"This does not put us on a pathway to 2 degrees","depth":4},{"id":13,"text":"Samantha Smith , , WWF","depth":4},{"id":14,"text":"In the agreement , the Chinese promise not just to peak their emissions by 2030","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"but to increase the share of non-fossil fuels in their energy mix to 20 % by the same date .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"Strangely , earlier this year a report from analysts GlobalData suggested","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"that China is already on course to get 20 % of its energy from greener sources by 2020 .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"The agreement does marks a significant moment","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"with China , for the first time , naming a date","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"when their emissions will peak .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"But the deal does n't stem from a philosophical determination","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"to save the planet .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"It is based on the naked political necessities of both countries .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"President Obama needs to show the US Congress and public","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"he can create a level playing field","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"for American industry to compete with China .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"President Xi Jinping needs to show the Chinese people","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"that he is making significant efforts","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"to clean the air","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"by reducing the use of coal ,","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"while maintaining China 's efforts","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"to lift people out of poverty .","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"But in terms of steering the world to below the 2 degree C target","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"that scientists believe","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"is the threshold of danger ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"this agreement does n't cut the mustard .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"`` This does not put us on a pathway to 2 degrees , ''","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"said Samantha Smith from WWF .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"`` This announcement is a political signal from these two countries .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"If we understand it as a signal ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"it is a good thing","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"and it is a first for China","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"to stand up","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"and say","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"it will cap it 's emissions . ''","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"The China-US step also received a muted welcome from the Alliance of Small Island States ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"( Aosis )","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"made up of countries","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"facing threats from rising sea levels .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"`` We look forward to more detailed information","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"about how the commitments match up against what is needed","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"to ensure a safe global climate , ''","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"the Aosis ministers said in a statement .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"`` We recognise the importance of bilateral cooperation between these two countries ,","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"but the numbers must add up , ''","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"they added cautiously .","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"The real significance of the US-China deal is the changes","depth":3},{"id":58,"text":"it signals in the UN political process .","depth":3},{"id":59,"text":"Every nation has committed to agree a new deal by the time","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"the parties get together in Paris next year .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Next month the negotiators will meet in Peru","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"to draft the text of that agreement .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"What has blighted that whole process has been a very basic division over definitions","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"- who is rich and who is poor ?","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"The developed countries agree","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that they will take on the biggest burden of emissions cuts ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"but they insist","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"that the richer developing nations must do so too .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"This has been strongly resisted by many of these emerging economies , including India -","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"They point to the hundred of millions without electricity in their country","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"and say","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"they will resist attempts","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"to limit their use of coal ,","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"which they say","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"they need to develop .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"According to some observers ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"the Beijing deal is significant","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"because it underlines the fact","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that China is changing its position .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"`` It signals a shift , ''","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"according to Liz Gallagher from environmental think-tank E3G .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"`` At the highest level there is a recognition","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"that China is n't a deeply poor society","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"and that they are distinct from other developing countries . `` I would n't say","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"they have lumped themselves in with the US and EU ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"it is almost like a transition","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"they have committed to . ''","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"As well as putting pressure on the developing countries","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"to move on from a simple , binary view of the world ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"the deal should also put pressure on some developed countries","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"who have been moving away from tackling emissions .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"`` The ball is in play ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"so now others , not just developing counties","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"but the likes of Japan , Canada and Australia , there is now pressure on them to come forward with something themselves , ''","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"said Samantha Smith .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"Taken together with the EU 's recent announcement of new climate targets for 2030 ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"you could be forgiven for thinking","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"that a deal in Paris is in the bag .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"Cutting emissions is just one part of the negotiations , and for many countries , the least important bit .","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"For many , the bigger questions are about cash","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"to cope with the impact of climate change .","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"Many nations want a financial mechanism","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"that would put a legal responsibility on those","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"who have done most","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"to cause climate change","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"to compensate those","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"who suffer most from it .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"This is a potential iceberg for the whole process .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"`` There is a need for the developing countries to see","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"that there would be certainty in terms of future flows of finance ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"otherwise we wo n't see much ownership of this process from many of the parties in Paris , ''","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"said Tosi Mpanu-Mpanu , a senior negotiator from the Democratic Republic of Congo ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"speaking to me earlier this year .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":227,"left":170,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":127,"right":169,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":125,"right":126,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":120,"right":124,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":120,"left":117,"right":119,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":0,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":1,"right":115,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":115,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":118,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":118,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":11,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":121,"right":122,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":158,"right":168,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":130,"right":157,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":130,"left":128,"right":129,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"le